</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<collectingCountry id="4BBE7643FF941D5C7828FA35FDDB0D82" box="[537,634,1467,1491]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="3" pageNumber="312">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
(A. H. 
<bibRefCitation id="57384B22FF941D5C78F6FA35FF710DA5" author="Clark, A. H." pageId="3" pageNumber="312" pagination="1 - 82" refId="ref17978" refString="Clark, A. H. 1931. A monograph of the existing crinoids. Volume 1. The comatulids. Part 3. Superfamily Comasterida. Bulletin of the Unit- ed States National Museum 82: i - vii + 1 - 816, pls 1 - 82." type="journal article" year="1931">Clark 1931</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7BB36558FF941D5C7A84FA72FE4E0EC7" pageId="3" pageNumber="312" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="331636D3FF941D5C7A84FA72FE4E0EC7" blockId="3.[156,768,621,1686]" pageId="3" pageNumber="312">
<emphasis id="01DDEAC1FF941D5C7A84FA72FEB80E45" bold="true" box="[181,281,1532,1556]" pageId="3" pageNumber="312">Remarks.</emphasis>
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="F4A94D50FF941D5C7B5AFA73FDD80E45" authority="L. Agassiz, 1836" authorityName="L. Agassiz" authorityYear="1836" box="[363,633,1532,1556]" class="Crinoidea" family="Comasteridae" genus="Comaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Comatulida" pageId="3" pageNumber="312" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="01DDEAC1FF941D5C7B5AFA73FE6B0E45" box="[363,458,1533,1556]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="312">Comaster</emphasis>
L. Agassiz, 1836
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by having numerous arms with the first syzygy at br 
<subScript id="AF2D3496FF941D5C78D1F9A6FD5B0E67" attach="left" box="[736,762,1576,1590]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="312">3+4</subScript>
, asymmetric bifurcation beyond IIIBr series, and the central mass integrated by interradial plates. This species is unique in almost lacking functional cirri.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
